Peru says first half oil output up , natgas down . Peru produced an average of 121 , 698 barrels per day ( bpd ) of crude oil in the first half , up 2 . 5 percent from the same period last year , the Energy and Mines Ministry said Thursday . Natural gas output between January and June averaged 20 . 44 million cubic feet per day , down 1 . 5 percent from the first half last year , the ministry added in a monthly report . ( ( - - Andrew Cawthorne , Lima newsroom , 511 221 - 2134 ) ) 
